spec: multiprocessing_extra108
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/queues.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra107.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 254 theme — multiprocessing.JoinableQueue class identity (subclass of Queue) and multiprocessing.queues module class hierarchy. NEW in extra108: multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__name__=='Queue', __bases__[0].__name__=='object', __mro__.__len__()==2, __module__=='multiprocessing.queues'; multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__name__=='JoinableQueue', __bases__[0].__name__=='Queue', __mro__.__len__()==3, __module__=='multiprocessing.queues'; multiprocessing.queues.SimpleQueue.__name__=='SimpleQueue', __bases__[0].__name__=='object', __mro__.__len__()==2, __module__=='multiprocessing.queues'; type(multiprocessing.queues.Queue.get).__name__=='function', Queue.get.__qualname__=='Queue.get' (len=9, co_argcount=3: self, block, timeout); type(multiprocessing.queues.Queue.put).__name__=='function', Queue.put.__qualname__=='Queue.put' (len=9, co_argcount=4: self, obj, block, timeout); JoinableQueue.join.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.join' (len=18, co_argcount=1: self only); JoinableQueue.task_done.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.task_done' (len=23, longest qualname in spec, co_argcount=1: self only). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. Queue inherits directly from object (MRO=[Queue, object], length=2). Queue.get has co_argcount=3 (self, block, timeout); Queue.put has co_argcount=4 (self, obj, block, timeout). Queue.__module__=='multiprocessing.queues'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Queue'. JoinableQueue inherits from Queue (MRO=[JoinableQueue, Queue, object], length=3). JoinableQueue adds join() and task_done() methods for task tracking. JoinableQueue.join.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.join' (len=18, co_argcount=1); JoinableQueue.task_done.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.task_done' (len=23, longest qualname in spec, co_argcount=1). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.queues.SimpleQueue.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. SimpleQueue inherits directly from object (MRO=[SimpleQueue, object], length=2, same as Queue). SimpleQueue is a simpler queue with fewer methods than Queue. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing.queues.Queue class identity — extra108
#
# Wave 254 theme: Queue, JoinableQueue, SimpleQueue class identity.
#
# multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__name__              == 'Queue'   (base=object, mro len=2)
# multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__name__      == 'JoinableQueue' (base=Queue, mro len=3)
# multiprocessing.queues.SimpleQueue.__name__        == 'SimpleQueue'   (base=object, mro len=2)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

